ears of a wicked Nineveh, Jonah, appalled at the hostility he should raise, 
fled from his mission, and sought to escape his duty and his God by taking ship 
at Joppa. But God is everywhere; Tarshish he never reached. As we have seen, 
God came upon him in the whale, and swallowed him down to living gulfs of doom, 
and with swift slantings tore him along ‘into the midst of the seas,’ where 
